  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6765 sitting right on the max negative gamma strike (-15.2B), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma position demands flow-following hedging in this breakout regime. The massive negative gamma wall from 6755-6770 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any directional move gets accelerated by dealer hedging, while 6780 represents the critical flip point where dealers switch to selling pressure (+7.9B positive gamma). The gex_surge event combined with -221.7% five-minute GEX change signals violent dealer rebalancing is underway, favoring continuation of the current move rather than mean reversion.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect amplified moves in whichever direction breaks first, with 6780 as the key battle line.",
